        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer338239427" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4115413433818670031">The Restorer&apos;s Son Expanded Edition is the icing on the cake! For those of us who&apos;ve come to love the folks of Braide Wood (&amp; will admit to having gotten so thoroughly engaged in the stories, that we found ourselves praying for &quot;Kiearan&quot; and other characters in our daily quiet times!), RSEE (Restorer&apos;s Son Expanded Edition) is everything we loved about the original, and all that we secretly hoped would be added, since we couldn&apos;t get enough of the characters and stories the first time around! :-</span>
  <span id="freeText4115413433818670031" style="display:none">The Restorer's Son Expanded Edition is the icing on the cake! For those of us who've come to love the folks of Braide Wood (&amp; will admit to having gotten so thoroughly engaged in the stories, that we found ourselves praying for "Kiearan" and other characters in our daily quiet times!), RSEE (Restorer's Son Expanded Edition) is everything we loved about the original, and all that we secretly hoped would be added, since we couldn't get enough of the characters and stories the first time around! :-)<br /><br />I admit to being a bit of a Kieran fangirl (he's a bit Mr. Darcy, a bit Han Solo...exasperating and enchanting all at once!), so this book is a particular favorite in the series.<br /><br />I majored in English in college &amp; took one whole semester of Lewis &amp; Tolkien as my textbooks, so my taste in spec fic is pretty high &amp; picky...!!<br /><br />Sharon Hinck joins an elite list of my favorite authors who know how to use the vehicle of fiction to tell the One True Story &amp; to tell it well. Thank you, Sharon!! </span>
  <a data-text-id="4115413433818670031" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


