              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5153228588705201440">3.5 stars<br/>This book was good, but not as good as the first book in the series. It was very enjoyable read, a bit slow at times and some of the story lines didn&apos;t really work as well as I thought they should. I enjoy Sharon Hinck&apos;s writing! It is so refreshing and enjoyable! She is so in tune to real life that it bleeds into her stories and makes them that much more relatable. I love her humor and her characters sass and sarcasm. It ended on such a cliff-hanger that I was so grateful I had book 3 </span>
  <span id="freeText5153228588705201440" style="display:none">3.5 stars<br />This book was good, but not as good as the first book in the series. It was very enjoyable read, a bit slow at times and some of the story lines didn't really work as well as I thought they should. I enjoy Sharon Hinck's writing! It is so refreshing and enjoyable! She is so in tune to real life that it bleeds into her stories and makes them that much more relatable. I love her humor and her characters sass and sarcasm. It ended on such a cliff-hanger that I was so grateful I had book 3 on hand! If you read book one, definitely give this one a read because you need to read book 3 which is even better! <br /><br />~Contains some violence and brief/vague mentions of a premarital relationship.</span>
